{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/apply-is-for-building-things3/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Daniel Talks Code"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7af123f3-0bc3-5cee-8803-04e00179cb50","excerpt":"One of the things I‚Äôve wanted to improve on is my use of Kotlin Scope functions in my everyday workflow. And so I decided to start a short series where I‚Äôll‚Ä¶","html":"<p>One of the things I‚Äôve wanted to improve on is my use of Kotlin Scope functions in my everyday workflow. And so I decided to start a short series where I‚Äôll talk about how to use each of the functions along with an example or two.</p>\n<p>Starting with the <a href=\"https://kotlinlang.org/docs/scope-functions.html#apply\"><code class=\"language-text\">.apply</code></a> scope function, it is useful for building objects as it applies the actions within the corresponding lambda to the object that it is called on. It doesn‚Äôt return a value, but instead you get the object itself. Which means you can both declare a new object and ‚Äúapply‚Äù multiple actions on it at the same time.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"kotlin\"><pre class=\"language-kotlin\"><code class=\"language-kotlin\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token function\">NinjaTurtle</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> String<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> String<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> weapon<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> String<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">fun</span> <span class=\"token function\">training</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string-literal singleline\"><span class=\"token string\">\"</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">$</span><span class=\"token expression\">name</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> is now a ninja!\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">fun</span> <span class=\"token function\">feed</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string-literal singleline\"><span class=\"token string\">\"</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">$</span><span class=\"token expression\">name</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> loves üçï!\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">fun</span> <span class=\"token function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>args<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> Array<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> donnie <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">NinjaTurtle</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"token string-literal singleline\"><span class=\"token string\">\"Donatello\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string-literal singleline\"><span class=\"token string\">\"purple\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token string-literal singleline\"><span class=\"token string\">\"bo\"</span></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">apply</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">training</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">feed</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":".apply is for building things","date":"March 03, 2021","description":null,"featuredImage":{"src":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/9ec227057553b868bcbe00e4b940f263/b78d2/illustration-of-apply-scope-function.jpg","srcSet":"/static/9ec227057553b868bcbe00e4b940f263/d5af9/illustration-of-apply-scope-function.jpg 625w,\n/static/9ec227057553b868bcbe00e4b940f263/271b9/illustration-of-apply-scope-function.jpg 1250w,\n/static/9ec227057553b868bcbe00e4b940f263/b78d2/illustration-of-apply-scope-function.jpg 2500w","sizes":"(min-width: 2500px) 2500px, 100vw"},"sources":[]},"width":2500,"height":1471}}},"alt":"Illustration of the .apply scope function by Daniel Perez-Gomez"}}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/what-is-state-in-programming/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"What is State in programming?"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/perform-additional-tasks-with-an-object-using-also/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Perform additional tasks with an object using .also"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"7af123f3-0bc3-5cee-8803-04e00179cb50","previousPostId":"4960980d-edb4-5b9d-b0c3-2f0e10c74759","nextPostId":"866